item title: Vestil SKB-DLX Deluxe Steel Pallet Buster with Handle, 41&quot;
review: I have been busting up pallets and reusing the wood for years.  Rubber mallets and wrecking bars, pry bars, sawsalls, jigsaws, hammers, catspaws, you name it and i have used it.  Sometimes I have been very successful, others not so much.  I have a surface planner so nail removal is vital for me.  I have never been able to reuse the stringers because nail removal is next to impossible...until now.  This puppy not only removes planks like the nuts but leaves nailheads intact and super easy to pull with a pry bar.  I used to spend a hour min. on a pallet.  Now 15 mins is the max and most pallets are done in 10.  I have a better board retention rate and stringers are actually usable.  I wish I had stumbled across this years ago.
